# This file intentionally keeps an empty `public/` directory in git.
#
# Vercel deploys this backend as a serverless API (the Express app lives in
# api/index.ts and is bundled by @vercel/node). Because the project has no
# framework preset, Vercel still runs a build phase and then validates a static
# "Output Directory" — defaulting to `public`. If that directory does not exist,
# the deploy fails with:
#
#   Error: No Output Directory named "public" found after the Build completed.
#
# Committing this directory guarantees the Output Directory exists regardless of
# whether the vercel.json buildCommand runs, so the check always passes. The
# directory stays empty on purpose: the catch-all rewrite in vercel.json sends
# every request to the api/ function, so nothing is ever served statically.
#
# Do not delete this file.
